data.title: 17th St Location
data.text: I ordered delivery. It took a lot longer than it should have and when the kid dropped it off he went off complaining about his boss. Super unprofessional. Then the food was disgusting. The "lemon chicken" used the kind of lemon pudding sauce you get out of a can that fills doughnuts or pies, but not a good quality one. Pretty much all of their food is just canned or frozen, nothing fresh or actually made at the "restaurant". I like my food and will just about anything, but my $16 dinner (that I expected to be around $11 after the tip so not sure what happened there) went to the garbage

data.title: Horrible customer service
data.text: We ordered carry out it being my first time eating there. We had 5 meals 3 of which were messed up and missing items. So we called thinking we would be able to get the missing items. Instead we got a rude lady on the phone that argued with us and told us we were wrong. Told us if we wanted the missing items we would have to pay for them even though we had already payed for them. They ended up giving the phone over to 3 different people and everyone of them was nasty to us and wanted nothing to do with getting us the product that we had paid for. I will never order food from them again, and they should think about getting better people to work the front that have better customer service.

data.title: Authentic Chinese Restaurant in the Heart of Idaho Falls.  The food was very fresh and delicious!
data.text: We had a great authentic Chinese meal in a very clean, classic building in the heart of downtown Idaho Falls!  Be sure to bring your appetite, you won't be disappointed. The owners obviously take great pride in their dishes. Everything was fresh and flavorful.

data.title: Delicious!
data.text: This was my first time here. The food was incredible; some of the best I've ever had. I will definitely be going back.

data.title: Average Chinese Food
data.text: Here you can dine in, carry out, or get delivery food. The food is what you'd expect given that type of business. When I crave Chinese food I do order delivery but don't expect authentic Chinese food.

data.title: Alway Fresh and Spicy to Taste
data.text:
Another favorite for a nice lunch, dinner  or takeout.  Located downtown or on 17th Street, Happy's offers a nice selection of dishes at a reasonable price.  Spicy dishes can be toned down or heated up to taste.  Fresh vegetables and really good lo mein.

Also, downtown location offers beer and wine.  

Best chinese in Idaho Falls!

data.title: Never a bad meal
data.text: This restaurant is reasonable and has great fresh tasting food. The service is good and quick. I always am pleased.

data.title: Authentic Chinese
data.text: The chef/owner and his are from China where he trained and is certified as a chef. His food is delicious and his recipes are original. Many of the dishes can be spiced as hot as you want. Portions are generous and prices are reasonable. Combo plates are a great way to try several dishes!

data.title: Best eggroll I have ever had!!
data.text: We ate at the Happy's in downtown Idaho Falls for dinner. It is located in a renovated historic space that may be beat described as Asian art deco". We both ordered one of the combination platters for $8.95 which  were nicely presented with very generous portions. The eggroll and the fried shrimp were both outstanding !! The lo mein was light and tasty and not the heavy ,dense noodles you find in the food court of a local mall... We will definitely return!

data.title: Deserves Zero Stars - HORRIBLE!
data.text: 17th Street Happy's Express.  Same owners.  Worst food I have ever eaten.  Everything we ordered had a horrible rancid flavor like it had been cooked in really bad old, rancid oil.  We tried the chicken, beef, loo mein and fried rice.  All of it had the same horrible flavor.  When I called about it asking if I could take the order back (that we only ate maybe 10 bites total of), they were extremely rude.  Said they would only give me other food or nothing.  It was not their fault we didn't like it.  They refused to give us a refund then hung up on me.  I WILL NEVER RETURN!!!!

data.title: Great restaurant, new location
data.text: We love this restaurant. It is the best Chinese food in town. Also, it just changed locations. It is now on the corner of Shoup and B street.

data.title: Good solid Chinese food
data.text:
This to my understanding is the only Chinese delivery in Idaho falls .

Service was fast .

Great food

data.title: Tasty and they delivered
data.text:
We were tired  and wanted good food that was not pizza that would deliver. Happy's fit the bill. They delivered (we stayed at the 
Best Western, Driftwood Inn). Good food, but a tiny bit pricey,

data.title: Both locations have great food
data.text: Happy Chinese is a well known institution in Idaho Falls for great Chinese food.  Now that they have a 2nd location on 17th Street, there are more choices to enjoy. The Take-out choice offers a great alternative to hamburgers and tacos, bringing us great food at very reasonable prices, and fast service with a kind smile. The servings are very generous and makes this fast-food choice a wonderful value. Another thing I enjoy about eating at Happy Chinese is that I know they are not part of a large chain and their food is made fresh and to my request. I like supporting my "Idaho Falls neighbors" and keeping my dollars spent in my own community. I recommend either location for great Chinese food.

data.title: Best Chinese Ever!
data.text: I have never eaten better Chinese Food. Their sweet and sour chicken is Devine. Their Concubine Chicken is like nothing you have ever tasted. I do not agree with other posters about bad service. I have never seen bad service there. You get seated immediately. They are friendly and check on you often. They even remember us and our families, asking about other family members when they don't come with us. They are even great when serving Gluten Free. Including their new GF Sweet and Sour Chicken.

data.title: Love the food, Hate the service
data.text: As a frequent customer of Happy's I love their food. However, I usually go in and take it to go. If you stay in and eat their service stinks and the restaurant has no atmosphere. I attempted to order for delivery and the owner and woman were extremely rude when I asked if a substitution was possible with an extra charge. I was yelled at and talked over. I will not be recommending them again, nor will I be spending my hard earned money there. IF you have good food, it doesn't mean everything, you need to provide excellent customer service to keep your customers coming back! 4 star rating for food, zero stars for service.

data.title: Good Food But No Atmosphere
data.text: With the exception of their combination plates, which are pretty ordinary like almost all Chinese restaurants I've been to, most of their menu selections are very good. The service can sometimes be inconsistent but the food is worth it. The food offsets the lack of ambience at this restaurant.

data.title: Excellent
data.text: The food here is great.  Not much ambience, tasty and well presented.  We ate here on a Friday night and we had street entertainment - bagpipers.

data.title: Chinese
data.text: I had the chicken fried rice, was spicy and delicious.

data.title: Love Happy Chinese!
data.text:
I love this restaurant. The food is amazing. We have a dozen Chinese restaurants in Idaho Falls and my Chinese grad student recommended this one as the best. We were not disappointed. Awesome! 

I would also like to review Happy Chinese Express in Idaho Falls, Idaho but I can't find it on Trip Advisor. It is also amazing and is the cleanest restaurant in Idaho Falls.
